@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="legal-page">
    <nav class="legal-nav">
        <a href="/" class="legal-brand">
            <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="LifeAdvisor" class="auth-logo-img legal-brand-logo" />
            <span class="brand-text">LifeAdvisor</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/" class="legal-back">← Back to home</a>
    </nav>

    <article class="legal-container">
        <header class="legal-header">
            <span class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</span>
            <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="legal-meta">Last updated 20 June 2026</p>
        </header>

        <div class="legal-notice">
            This is a working draft for an early-stage product and is not legal advice. It explains, in
            plain language, how LifeAdvisor handles your information today. We will update it as the
            product matures.
        </div>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
            <p>
                LifeAdvisor is a personal decision-guidance tool. It builds a private model of you — your
                "digital twin" — from the information you choose to share, and uses it to help you think
                through important life decisions. This policy covers the LifeAdvisor application and the
                data you give us while using it.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
            <p>We only collect what we need to run the service:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your email address and a securely hashed password. We never store your password in plain text.</li>
                <li><strong>Your profile and onboarding answers</strong> — your preferred name, life stage, and the life areas you choose to focus on.</li>
                <li><strong>The content you write</strong> — the decisions, values, goals, and personal context you enter so your twin can give relevant guidance.</li>
                <li><strong>Derived data</strong> — mathematical representations (embeddings) of your text, used to find decisions related to the one you're facing.</li>
                <li><strong>Technical data</strong> — an essential session cookie that keeps you signed in, plus basic server logs needed for security and reliability.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To build and update your digital twin.</li>
                <li>To generate guidance and model possible outcomes for the decisions you bring to us.</li>
                <li>To surface relevant decisions from your own history.</li>
                <li>To create and secure your account.</li>
                <li>To maintain, debug, and improve the service.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information, and we do not use your private content to advertise to you.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>4. AI processing and third parties</h2>
            <p>
                To generate guidance and the embeddings described above, the text you submit is sent to a
                third-party AI model provider for processing. That provider processes your content only to
                return a result to LifeAdvisor. We share the minimum needed to perform the request, and we
                do not give third parties the right to use your content for their own purposes beyond
                providing the service to us.
            </p>
            <p>
                Please avoid entering information you would not want processed by an external model, such as
                government identifiers, payment card numbers, or another person's private details.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>5. How your data is stored and protected</h2>
            <p>
                Your data is stored in our database and protected with industry-standard practices,
                including hashed passwords and access controls. LifeAdvisor is early-stage software under
                active development, so we are honest that our safeguards will keep improving over time. No
                online service can promise perfect security.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>6. Your choices and rights</h2>
            <p>You stay in control of your data. At any time you can ask us to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Access a copy of the information associated with your account.</li>
                <li>Correct information that is inaccurate.</li>
                <li>Delete your content or close your account entirely.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To make a request, contact us using the details below.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
            <p>
                We keep your information for as long as your account is active. When you delete content or
                close your account, we remove the associated data from our active systems within a
                reasonable period, except where we must retain limited records for security or legal reasons.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>8. Children</h2>
            <p>
                LifeAdvisor is intended for adults. It is not directed at children under 16, and we do not
                knowingly collect information from them.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
            <p>
                As LifeAdvisor evolves, we may update this policy. When we make a material change, we will
                revise the "last updated" date above and, where appropriate, notify you in the app.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
            <p>
                Questions about your privacy or this policy? Reach us at
                <a href="mailto:support@lifeadvisor.app">support@lifeadvisor.app</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>

    <footer class="legal-footer">
        <span>© 2026 LifeAdvisor</span>
        <span class="legal-footer-links">
            <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        </span>
    </footer>
</div>
